Class IInsertSelectBuilder

  • gw.api.database.IInsertSelectBuilder

  • public class IInsertSelectBuilder
    Performs an Insert-Select

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      IQueryBuilder<Bean> SourceQuery
      the query used for the source

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int execute()
      Executes the query. If already in a transaction, the query executes in that transaction; otherwise a new transaction is created and committed when the method returns, or rolled back if the method throws an exception. The statement that is constructed will perform default behavior for the following fields (if present and not mapped):- ID (keyable beans only): using new keys from the KeyGenerator PublicID (keyable beans only): default public id prefix followed by a ':' followed by the numeric ID BeanVersion (versionable beans only): 0 CreateTime (editable beans only): current time CreateUser (editable beans only): the current user UpdateTime (editable beans only): current time UpdateUser (editable beans only): the current user Retired (retireable beans only): 0 Columns with default values that are not mapped will be inserted with their default values. In a multi-threaded environment, you may get an exception if the number of rows updated does not match the expected row count (determined by the query portion of the statement). You may also get an exception regarding duplicate ID if the number of rows updated exceeds the expected row count as the statement may use IDs from other concurrent inserts.
      IInsertSelectBuilder mapColumn(IEntityPropertyInfo targetColumn, Object source)
      Maps the value of the target column to the value of the source
      IInsertSelectBuilder withDescription(String descriptionForTheQuery)
      Sets a string describing the query. Useful for debugging performance issues.
      IInsertSelectBuilder withInsertHint(boolean withInsertHint)
      Whether to append NOLOG hint in the generated SQL (Oracle only). This behavior may be turned off globally in the configuration.
      IInsertSelectBuilder withLogSQL(boolean logSQL)
      Turns on or off SQL logging. The query is logged to the PLLoggerCategory.SERVER_DATABASE log category at the info level
      IInsertSelectBuilder withParallelDml(boolean useParallelDml)
      Use parallel DML when executing this statement (Oracle only). This behavior may be turned off globally in the configuration by setting the ora-parallel-dml attribute on the upgrade element to "disable". It may also be overridden with the parallel-dml attribute of the versiontrigger element.
